@Churchills Dog:

Take my case for example..  Got it for xmas, but of course was pre-order.  Was sent to me from the US once they got it (couldn't pre-order to Canada), but UPS comes to my door wanting $42 in taxes and fees, I reject.  Now I download it and when it arrives back in the US, I will phone and ask them to open and read me the CD key.

Moral of the story: UPS blows, torrents are good and can be used for legit reasons!
